Delete is preserved with ~…~ — dropping it would flip the meaning of the sentence.
```
The build is {-broken-} working.
.
The build is ~broken~ working.
```

Single-token superscript uses leading ^ (standard ASCII math convention).
```
x^2^ is squared.
.
x^2 is squared.
```

Single-token subscript uses leading _ (H_2O etc.).
```
H~2~O is water.
.
H_2O is water.
```

Multi-token superscript wraps in parens to keep the scope explicit.
```
x^n + 1^ is the thing.
.
x^(n + 1) is the thing.
```

Multi-token subscript wraps in parens.
```
f~i, j~ is a matrix element.
.
f_(i, j) is a matrix element.
```
